here soon. Look.

21:29.335 --> 21:31.251
-(laughing):
They are so cute!
-The Guy: Aw.

21:31.335 --> 21:32.835
They have their
heads shaved!

21:32.919 --> 21:34.669
Oh yeah, in solidarity.

21:34.752 --> 21:36.835
Did... Did Bryan
shave his head?

21:38.335 --> 21:39.960
No?

21:40.043 --> 21:41.377
-Oh, insecure man.
-That's right.

21:41.460 --> 21:42.919
You gotta get
on the train, man.

21:43.001 --> 21:45.960
It's just people who come
here from all over the world

21:46.043 --> 21:48.085
to meet with this
one specialist.

21:48.168 --> 21:52.752
-Mm-hmm.
-Yeah, and everybody
is so gentle and quiet.

21:52.835 --> 21:54.293
It's actually
very, very nice.

21:54.377 --> 21:56.669
-I mean, I'm so glad
you guys found him.
-I know, right?

21:56.752 --> 21:59.669
-Bryan: Hey! Bruh!
-Sarah: Hi!

21:59.752 --> 22:01.043
-The Guy: Hey!
-What's up?

22:01.126 --> 22:02.835
-Good to see you, man!
-Nice to see you!

22:02.919 --> 22:04.919
Bryan:
How's it going?
Hey, Lo! Come here.

22:05.001 --> 22:07.126
-Oh, yeah.
-Oh, hey!

22:07.210 --> 22:09.043
-Hey, Lo!
-Yeah.

22:09.126 --> 22:11.919
Hey, remember, we gotta
pick up that medicine from
the fridge to keep at Ronald.

22:12.001 --> 22:13.377
Oh yeah, got it.
I almost lost

22:13.460 --> 22:15.502
a bottle of medicine that
cost... (whispers): $10,000.

22:15.585 --> 22:17.001
-Yeah. A lot.
-Uh-oh.

22:17.085 --> 22:18.835
(laughing):
A lot. Yeah.

22:18.919 --> 22:20.585
Uh, listen, this was great.

22:20.669 --> 22:23.001
I really enjoyed getting to
hang out with this little bro.

22:23.085 --> 22:25.669
-Yeah, you meet
my friend here, Lo?
-Yeah.

22:25.752 --> 22:27.794
What do you think?
He still smell like pickles?

22:27.877 --> 22:30.919
-Bro, bro.
-(laughing): Sorry.

22:31.001 --> 22:33.210
-(laughing)
-A little bit?
A little bit?

22:33.293 --> 22:34.919
-All right, all right.
-Smells like pickles
a little bit?

22:35.001 --> 22:37.627
That is an open wound.
You can't just pour salt
like that.

22:37.710 --> 22:40.877
-I know, yeah.
-Listen, I want to help out.
Whatever I can do.

22:40.960 --> 22:43.794
We're gonna put the boys down
at Ronald and then we'll go out.

22:43.877 --> 22:45.335
'Cause I can also
come to Ronald.

22:45.418 --> 22:47.669
-It's not a problem
at all.
-Bro.

22:47.752 --> 22:49.210
-All right, well--
-We're gonna go out.

22:49.293 --> 22:50.502
You wanna get
something to eat?

22:50.585 --> 22:52.752
(all laughing)

22:52.835 --> 22:55.335
Payback! Sucka!

22:55.418 --> 22:57.627
Yeah, that was cool.
What'd you think of that, Logan?

22:57.710 --> 22:59.126
Oh, he liked it.

22:59.210 --> 23:00.502
-(laughing)
-Is this illegal?

23:00.585 --> 23:03.960
(bells tolling)

23:06.251 --> 23:07.835
Bruh.

23:07.919 --> 23:10.377
-Bruh.
-Bruh.

23:10.460 --> 23:12.710
-Marlboro Lights, huh?
-Mm-hmm.

23:12.794 --> 23:14.293
You used to smoke Camels.

23:16.335 --> 23:18.835
It's whatever.
I don't really care.

23:18.919 --> 23:20.502
Want some of this?

23:21.794 --> 23:25.126
-Cop's right there.
-Hospital's right there.

23:26.710 --> 23:28.335
So what do you
want to do, bruh?

23:29.752 --> 23:31.585
-Anything.
-(laughing)

23:31.669 --> 23:34.669
-You decide.
